    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Sports Editor:</p>
        <p>''Satellite TV Creates Sports Bar in the Sky'' (March 28) presents the increasing proliferation of television sets in public spaces as if it were a good thing. I beg to differ.</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>To the Sports Editor:</p>
        <p>''Satellite TV Creates Sports Bar in the Sky'' (March 28) presents the increasing proliferation of television sets in public spaces as if it were a good thing. I beg to differ.</p>
        <p>When traveling by air, it has become effectively impossible to avoid having a television set in one's line of sight either in the terminal or on the plane. JetBlue is one of the worst offenders. Count me as somebody who resents being a captive audience to advertising and vapid mass media: Not everybody wants to be locked into a sports bar as a way to get from place to place.</p>
        <p>Will Kinney  Buffalo</p>
      </block>
